    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix BWP release logic in UE configuration\n\n### Summary\nThe `release_dl_BWP()` and `release_ul_BWP()` functions were not working correctly due to incorrect array indexing and missing index adjustment after element removal. This caused BWP release operations to fail or release incorrect BWPs.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/config_ue.c`: Fixed array indexing bug in BWP release logic and added proper index adjustment after element removal\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure a UE with multiple BWPs\n2. Send a configuration update that includes a BWP release command\n3. Observe that incorrect BWPs are released or the release operation fails silently\n4. In some cases, this may lead to memory corruption or segmentation faults due to accessing invalid memory locations\n\nThe issue manifests as incorrect BWP management during reconfiguration procedures, potentially causing UE connection failures or unstable behavior when BWPs are dynamically reconfigured.\n"
}